\left \vert (AB)_{ik} \right \vert = \underbrace{\left \vert \sum_{j=1}^m a_{ij} b_{jk} \right \vert \leq \sum_{j=1}^m \vert a_{ij} \vert \vert b_{jk} \vert}_{\text{Triangle inequality}} = \overbrace{\sum_{j=1}^m \vert a_{ij} \vert \vert b_{jk} \vert \leq \sum_{j=1}^m \vert A \vert \vert B \vert}^{\text{Definition of $\vert A \vert $ and $\vert B \vert$}} = m\vert A \vert \vert B \vert
\max_{i,k}\left \vert (AB)_{ik} \right \vert \leq m\vert A \vert \vert B \vert
 |AB| = \max\{| \sum_{j=1}^{m}a_{ij}b_{jk} |: i = 1,...,n \text{ and} k = 1,...p\} \leq \max\{ \sum_{j=1}^{m}|a_{ij}b_{jk}| : i = 1,...,n \text{ and} k = 1,...p\}  \leq \max\{ \sum_{j=1}^{m}|a_{ij}||b_{jk}| : i = 1,...,n \text{ and} k = 1,...p\}\leq \max\{ \sum_{j=1}^{m}max\{|a_{ij}|\}max\{|b_{jk}|\}\}=max\{ \sum_{j=1}^{m}|A||B|\}=m|A||B|
